@page "/getting-started/mcp"

<PageTitle>MCP Server for AI coding agents | HAVIT Blazor Bootstrap - Free components for ASP.NET Core Blazor</PageTitle>
<DocHeadContent CanonicalRelativeUrl="/getting-started/mcp" />

<DocHeading Title="MCP Server" Level="1" />
<p class="lead">
	An MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that provides API documentation for HAVIT Blazor components.
	AI assistants (GitHub Copilot, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, etc.) can use this server to look up component parameters, properties, events, methods, and demo samples.
</p>
<p>
	The MCP server is available as a <strong>Premium</strong> feature.
	<a href="/premium">Learn more about Premium subscription.</a>
</p>

<DocHeading Title="Setup" Level="2" />
<p>Select your IDE to get customized instructions.</p>
<HxAlert Color="ThemeColor.Light">
	<p class="mb-0 fw-semibold"><small>IDE / AI assistant</small></p>
	<HxButtonGroup Size="ButtonGroupSize.Small" CssClass="mb-2">
		<InputRadioGroup @bind-Value="_ide">
			<InputRadio id="ideVsCode" class="btn-check" Value="@IdeChoice.VsCode" />
			<label class="btn btn-outline-primary" for="ideVsCode">VS Code</label>

			<InputRadio id="ideVs" class="btn-check" Value="@IdeChoice.VisualStudio" />
			<label class="btn btn-outline-primary" for="ideVs">Visual Studio</label>

			<InputRadio id="ideClaudeCode" class="btn-check" Value="@IdeChoice.ClaudeCode" />
			<label class="btn btn-outline-primary" for="ideClaudeCode">Claude Code</label>

			<InputRadio id="ideOther" class="btn-check" Value="@IdeChoice.Other" />
			<label class="btn btn-outline-primary" for="ideOther">Other</label>
		</InputRadioGroup>
	</HxButtonGroup>
</HxAlert>

@if (_ide == IdeChoice.VsCode)
{
	<p>
		Add to your <code>.vscode/mcp.json</code> (or user/workspace settings):
	</p>
	<CodeSnippet Language="json">{
  "servers": {
    "HAVIT Blazor Documentation": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://mcp.havit.blazor.eu"
    }
  }
}
</CodeSnippet>
	<p>
		See <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/chat/mcp-servers">Use MCP servers in VS Code</a> for more details.
	</p>
}
else if (_ide == IdeChoice.VisualStudio)
{
	<p>
		Add the following configuration to the <code>.mcp.json</code> file in the root of your solution or project directory
		(create the file if it doesn't exist):
	</p>
	<CodeSnippet Language="json">{
  "servers": {
    "HAVIT Blazor Documentation": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://mcp.havit.blazor.eu"
    }
  }
}
</CodeSnippet>
	<p>
		See <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/visualstudio/ide/mcp-servers">Use MCP servers in Visual Studio</a> for more details.
	</p>
}
else if (_ide == IdeChoice.ClaudeCode)
{
	<p>
		Add the server using the Claude Code CLI:
	</p>
	<CodeSnippet Language="none">claude mcp add --transport http "HAVIT Blazor Documentation" https://mcp.havit.blazor.eu</CodeSnippet>
	<p>
		Or add it manually to your <code>.mcp.json</code> file:
	</p>
	<CodeSnippet Language="json">{
  "mcpServers": {
    "HAVIT Blazor Documentation": {
      "type": "url",
      "url": "https://mcp.havit.blazor.eu"
    }
  }
}
</CodeSnippet>
	<p>
		See <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/agents-and-tools/claude-code/tutorials/set-up-mcp">Claude Code MCP documentation</a> for more details.
	</p>
}
else
{
	<p>
		For other AI-powered IDEs (Cursor, Windsurf, JetBrains, etc.), refer to their documentation on configuring HTTP MCP servers.
		The server URL is: <code>https://mcp.havit.blazor.eu</code>
	</p>	
}

<DocHeading Title="Available tools" Level="2" />

<DocHeading Title="get_component_docs" Level="3" />
<p>
	Returns the API documentation for a HAVIT Blazor component in Markdown format, including demo samples.
	Also resolves derived components with custom prefixes (e.g. <code>BtPager</code>, <code>PxButton</code>) to their base <code>Hx</code> component.
</p>

<DocHeading Title="get_type_doc" Level="3" />
<p>
	Returns the API documentation for a HAVIT Blazor supporting type (enum, settings class, delegate) in Markdown format.
</p>

<DocHeading Title="get_component_catalog" Level="3" />
<p>
	Returns a list of all HAVIT Blazor components (<code>Hx*</code>) with their name and summary description.
	No parameters required.
</p>

<DocHeading Title="get_component_samples" Level="3" />
<p>
	Returns all demo/sample code snippets (Razor source) for a HAVIT Blazor component.
	Also resolves derived components with custom prefixes (e.g. <code>BtPager</code>, <code>PxButton</code>) to their base <code>Hx</code> component.
</p>

<DocHeading Title="Testing" Level="2" />
<p>
	Once configured, you can ask your AI assistant about a component, for example:
	<i>"What parameters does HxButton have?"</i>
	The assistant should use the <code>get_component_docs</code> tool and return the API documentation.
</p>

